---
import BaseLayout from '../../components/BaseLayout.astro';
import TaxCalculator from '../../components/TaxCalculator.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
    title="The Local Closer: Data Center Tax Revenue | TomorrowBeginsHere.com"
    description="See how commercial property and equipment taxes from data centers fund public schools, emergency services, and roads, with concrete local impact examples."
>
    <!-- Page Header -->
    <div class="bg-slate-900 border-b border-tech-blue/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-emerald-950/80 via-slate-900/95 to-tech-blue/80 z-0 mix-blend-multiply"></div>
        <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-[url('/images/texas-data-centers-network.png')] bg-cover bg-center z-0 opacity-15 mix-blend-overlay"></div>
        <div class="relative z-10 max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-20 lg:py-24 text-center">
            <span class="inline-block px-4 py-1.5 rounded-full bg-emerald-500/20 text-emerald-300 font-bold tracking-widest uppercase text-sm mb-6 border border-emerald-500/30 backdrop-blur-sm">Pillar 03 • Local Tax Revenue</span>
            <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-bold text-white mb-6 tracking-tight leading-tight">
                The Tax Base is the Local Closer:<br><span class="text-emerald-300">Steel in the Ground Funds Our Future</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-slate-200 max-w-3xl mx-auto leading-relaxed font-light">
                Abstract economic theories don't pay for textbooks or emergency vehicles. Tangible, long-term commercial property and equipment taxes from data centers do.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Main Content -->
    <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-white relative">
        <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
            <div class="prose prose-lg prose-slate max-w-none">
                
                <p class="text-xl leading-relaxed text-slate-700 font-medium">
                    Data centers are massive, multi-decade capital investments. Because they require specialized structures, electrical gear, and cooling equipment, their assessed value is extremely high. In Texas, these facilities pay substantial real and personal property taxes, providing a critical source of funding for local public services.
                </p>

                <!-- Concrete local math callout -->
                <div class="bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl p-8 lg:p-10 my-12 shadow-sm">
                    <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6 border-b border-slate-100 pb-4">
                        The Concrete Math: What a Data Center Funds
                    </h3>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 mb-6">
                        Consider a standard **$1 Billion Hyperscale Data Center** built in a Texas county. Unlike residential subdivisions, which require millions in county services (schools, roads, water, policing), a data center requires minimal public resources.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-100 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-xs">
                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">School District Funding (ISD)</h4>
                            <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-emerald-600 mb-2">~$5.5M / year</div>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-0">
                                Directly funds local ISDs. This is equivalent to hiring **85+ new teachers**, purchasing **12 new school buses**, or fully funding school meal programs without raising tax rates for local families.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class="bg-white border border-slate-100 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-xs">
                            <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-800 mb-2">County & Emergency Services (ESD)</h4>
                            <div class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-emerald-600 mb-2">~$2.2M / year</div>
                            <p class="text-sm text-slate-500 mb-0">
                                Directly funds county road maintenance and Emergency Services Districts. This can buy **4 new fully-equipped fire engines** or fund county road paving programs.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-6">Commercial Value vs. Residential Strain</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    A typical 1,000-home subdivision adds about $300 million in property value, but it also adds over **1,500 new students** to the local ISD, floods county roads with daily traffic, and places heavy demands on water and sewer systems.
                </p>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    By comparison, a data center contributes three to four times the assessed taxable value, but places **zero new students** in local classrooms, adds virtually no daily traffic, and is guarded by self-contained private security. It represents the ultimate net community benefit: maximum tax generation with minimum service demand.
                </p>

                <!-- Tax Calculator Showcase -->
                <div class="my-16">
                    <div class="text-center max-w-2xl mx-auto mb-8">
                        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900">Estimate the Local Windfall</h3>
                        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600">Use our interactive calculator to see how different sizes of data center facilities translate to direct school district and emergency service funding.</p>
                    </div>
                    <TaxCalculator />
                </div>

                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-slate-900 mt-12 mb-6">Long-Term, Steel-in-the-Ground Stability</h2>
                <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                    Unlike standard businesses that can easily pack up and relocate, data centers are anchored by massive electrical infrastructure and concrete structures. Once an operator commits to a site, they are there for decades. Furthermore, servers and computing equipment must be refreshed every 3 to 5 years, which triggers ongoing sales and personal property tax revenue as new gear is installed.
                </p>

                <hr class="border-slate-200 my-12">

                <div class="text-center bg-slate-50 border border-slate-200 rounded-3xl p-8 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
                    <p class="text-slate-500 mb-4 uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-bold">Explore the next pillar</p>
                    <h4 class="text-lg font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Pillar 04: Reframe Against Realistic Alternatives</h4>
                    <a href="/texas-data-centers/realistic-alternatives" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-6 py-3 bg-tech-blue hover:bg-tech-blue/90 text-white font-bold rounded-xl transition-colors">
                        Next: Realistic Alternatives
                        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
                            <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2.5" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7" />
                        </svg>
                    </a>
                </div>

            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
